### Rebuilding broken ports ###

Now this is what I really would call a usefull feature helping to arrive at a more stable system: following up on an issue raised during today's [TROPOMI](/work/tropomi.html) progress meeting, I went back to a little something I already had started earlier last week, namely the extraction of a template for the new LaTeX documents. In order to simplify the creation of a new document (or even several thereof) the skeleton of the LaTeX source, alongside style packages, should be made available to everybody in the project to have a common starting point from which to continue editing.

Once the basic preparation of all source files was done, I went to check the resulting (PDF or Postscript) output... only to encounter a runtime error when firing up the LaTeX tool-chain:

~~~~
dyld: Library not loaded: /opt/local/lib/libtiff.3.dylib
  Referenced from: /opt/local/lib/libpoppler.34.dylib
  Reason: image not found
~~~~

Judging by the path to the shared library, this had to be a problem with my [MacPorts](http://www.macports.org) installation, though the specific error was something I could not remember having encountered before (at least not for a long while). Hence -- at least to my mind -- the next obvious thing to do, was trying to reinstall the package in question:

~~~~
sudo port install tiff
~~~~

However since the library was installed already the first part of the process went by rather quickly

